BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260328T102400
DTEND:20260328T130000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.963ft at 10:24\n-0.051ft at 13:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Morning starts off slow\, then a decent fresh blend of SSW swell and short
 er-period NW swell moves in\, for surf mainly running waist-stomach-chest 
 high in the afternoon\, while summertime focal points push head high\, sho
 wing largest late.  Dawn patrol is slowed by an early AM high tide. Mid da
 y gets drained by a negative low\, then incoming tide push helps through m
 uch of the afternoon. \n\nLight winds due all day\, variable in the mornin
 g\, southerly sea  breeze for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260328T161200
DTEND:20260328T190000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-0.077ft at 16:12\n-2.981ft at 19:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Morning starts off slow\, then a decent fresh blend of SSW swell and short
 er-period NW swell moves in\, for surf mainly running waist-stomach-chest 
 high in the afternoon\, while summertime focal points push head high\, sho
 wing largest late.  Dawn patrol is slowed by an early AM high tide. Mid da
 y gets drained by a negative low\, then incoming tide push helps through m
 uch of the afternoon. \n\nLight winds due all day\, variable in the mornin
 g\, southerly sea  breeze for the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260329T111800
DTEND:20260329T140000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.953ft at 11:18\n-0.015ft at 14:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 SSW Southern Hemi pulse eases\, along with NW swell. Widespread waist to s
 tomach high waves in the morning as standouts see better sets\, then surf 
 slowly winds down during the day. Mid morning is slowed by a high tide. Mi
 d afternoon gets drained by a negative low tide.  Best to plan around the 
 tide extremes. \n\nLight/variable winds most of the morning\, followed by 
 a light SW sea breeze in the afternoon. 
END:VEVENT
